#returns an array that holds the percent change based on the number of days inputted
def percentChange(closing_prices, days=1):
    result = [0]
    closing_prices = closing_prices.iloc[::days]
    
    for x in range(len(closing_prices)-1):
        result.append((closing_prices[x] - closing_prices[x+1])/closing_prices[x])
        
    return result
In [98]:
#compares 2 dictionary and finds the most smiliar ones
def find_similiar(list1, list2):
    for x in list1:
        most_similiar = 0 
        tuple_similiar = None

        for y in list2:
            similiar = np.intersect1d(list1[x], list2[y])    

            if len(similiar) > most_similiar:
                most_similiar = len(similiar)
                tuple_similiar = (x,y)
    
        print(tuple_similiar)
        try:
            list2.pop(tuple_similiar[1])
        except:
            break
In [99]:
#takes two dataframes and compares their corrleations with each other
def comparing_heatmaps(df1, df2):
    pv1 = df1.pivot_table(index='Ticker',
                   columns='Date',
                   values='Percent Change').fillna(0)
    pv2 = df2.pivot_table(index='Ticker',
                   columns='Date',
                   values='Percent Change').fillna(0)
    
    print('Sector:', df1['Sector'][0])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11, 9))
    sns.heatmap(pv1.transpose().corr(), vmin=-1, vmax=1, cmap="Blues", linewidth=0.3)
    plt.show()
    
    print('Sector:', df2['Predicted'][0])
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(11, 9))
    sns.heatmap(pv2.transpose().corr(), vmin=-1, vmax=1, cmap="Blues", linewidth=0.3)
    plt.show()
In [162]:
#gives a distrutions of sectors and tickers inside in pie format
def sectorDistrubtionsPie(sector_arr):
    data = {}
    count = 0 
    for num in (set(sector_arr)):
        for x in sector_arr:
            if x == num:
                count = count + 1 
        data[num] = count
    pie, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=[10,6])
    labels = data.keys()
    plt.pie(x=data.values(), labels=labels, colors= ['#00008B', '#1F75FE', '#7982B9', '#A5C1DC', '#E9F6FA','#74BBFB' ], textprops={'fontsize': 14})
    plt.title("Sector Distribution", fontsize=16);
    plt.show()

#Create a big dataframe with all information
tickers = QQQ['Holding Ticker'].to_numpy()
all_data = pd.DataFrame()
Q = QQQ.set_index('Holding Ticker')

for x in tickers:
    temp = pd.DataFrame()
    try: 
        temp = temp.append(yf.Ticker(x).history(start='2015-1-1', interval='1mo'))
    except Exception:
        continue 
        
    temp['Ticker'] = x
    sector = Q.loc[x]['Sector']
    temp['Sector'] = sector
    all_data = all_data.append(temp)
